  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Naomi Widowed'
      title: Naomi Widowed
      number: 1
      content: '  In the days when the judges governed [Israel], there was a famine
        in the land [of Canaan]. And a certain man of Bethlehem in Judah went to
        live temporarily in the country of Moab with his wife and his two sons. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "The man\u2019s name was Elimelech and his wife\u2019s name was Naomi
        and his two sons were named Mahlon and Chilion. They were Ephrathites from
        Bethlehem in Judah. They went to the country of Moab and stayed there. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then Elimelech, Naomi\u2019s husband, died, and she was left [a widow]
        with her two sons. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'They took wives from the Moabite women; the name of the one was Orpah,
        and the name of the other was Ruth. They lived there about ten years; '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'and then both Mahlon and Chilion also died, so the woman [Naomi]
        was left without her two sons and her husband.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Then she set out with her daughters-in-law to return from the country
        of Moab, for she had heard in Moab how the Lord had taken care of His people
        [of Judah] in giving them food. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'So she left the place where she was living, her two daughters-in-law
        with her, and they started on the way back to the land of Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "But Naomi said to her two daughters-in-law, \u201CGo back, each of
        you return to your mother\u2019s house. May the Lord show kindness to you
        as you have shown kindness to the dead and to me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "May the Lord grant that you find rest, each one in the home of her
        husband.\u201D Then she kissed them [goodbye], and they wept aloud. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And they said to her, \u201CNo, we will go with you to your people
        [in Judah].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "But Naomi said, \u201CGo back, my daughters, why should you go with
        me? Do I still have sons in my womb that may become your husbands? "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Go back, my daughters, go, for I am too old to have a husband. If
        I said I have hope, and if I actually had a husband tonight and even gave
        birth to sons, '
      comments: []
    - name: "13: Ruth\u2019s Loyalty"
      title: "Ruth\u2019s Loyalty"
      number: 13
      content: "would you wait until they were grown? Would you go without marrying?
        No, my daughters; for it is much more difficult for me than for you, because
        the Lord\u2019s hand has gone against me.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Then they wept aloud again; and Orpah kissed her mother-in-law [goodbye],
        but Ruth clung to her.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Then Naomi said, \u201CLook, your sister-in-law has gone back to
        her people and to her gods; turn back and follow your sister-in-law.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "But Ruth said, \u201CDo not urge me to leave you or to turn back
        from following you; for where you go, I will go, and where you lodge, I will
        lodge. Your people will be my people, and your God, my God. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Where you die, I will die, and there I will be buried. May the Lord
        do the same to me [as He has done to you], and more also, if anything but
        death separates me from you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'When Naomi saw that Ruth was determined to go with her, she said
        nothing more.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "So the two of them went on until they came to Bethlehem. And when
        they arrived in Bethlehem, the whole city was stirred because of them, and
        the women asked, \u201CIs this Naomi?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "She said to them, \u201CDo not call me Naomi (sweetness); call me
        Mara (bitter), for the Almighty has caused me great grief and bitterness. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "I left full [with a husband and two sons], but the Lord has brought
        me back empty. Why call me Naomi, since the Lord has testified against me
        and the Almighty has afflicted me?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: So Naomi returned from the country of Moab, and with her Ruth the
        Moabitess, her daughter-in-law. And they arrived in Bethlehem at the beginning
        of the barley harvest.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Ruth Gleans in Boaz\u2019 Field"
      title: "Ruth Gleans in Boaz\u2019 Field"
      number: 1
      content: '  Now Naomi had a relative of her husband, a man of great wealth
        and influence, from the family of Elimelech, whose name was Boaz. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And Ruth the Moabitess said to Naomi, \u201CPlease let me go to the
        field and glean among the ears of grain after one [of the reapers] in whose
        sight I may find favor.\u201D Naomi said to her, \u201CGo, my daughter.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'So Ruth went and picked up the leftover grain in a field after the
        reapers; and she happened to stop at the plot of land belonging to Boaz,
        who was of the family of Elimelech. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "It was then that Boaz came back from Bethlehem and said to the reapers,
        \u201CThe Lord be with you!\u201D And they answered him, \u201CThe Lord bless
        you!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then Boaz said to his servant who was in charge of the reapers, \u201CWhose
        young woman is this?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "The servant in charge of the reapers answered, \u201CShe is the young
        Moabite woman who came back with Naomi from the country of Moab. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And she said, \u2018Please let me glean and gather after the reapers
        among the sheaves.\u2019 So she came and has continued [gathering grain]
        from early morning until now, except when she sat [resting] for a little
        while in the [field] house.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then Boaz said to Ruth, \u201CListen carefully, my daughter. Do not
        go to glean in another field or leave this one, but stay here close by my
        maids. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Watch which field they reap, and follow behind them. I have commanded
        the servants not to touch you. And when you are thirsty, go to the [water]
        jars and drink from what the servants draw.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Then she kneeled face downward, bowing to the ground, and said to
        him, \u201CWhy have I found favor in your eyes that you should notice me,
        when I am a foreigner?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Boaz answered her, \u201CI have been made fully aware of everything
        that you have done for your mother-in-law since the death of your husband,
        and how you have left your father and mother and the land of your birth,
        and have come to a people that you did not know before. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "May the Lord repay you for your kindness, and may your reward be
        full from the Lord, the God of Israel, under whose wings you have come to
        take refuge.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Then she said, \u201CLet me find favor in your sight, my lord, for
        you have comforted me and have spoken kindly to your maidservant, though
        I am not as one of your maidservants.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "At mealtime Boaz said to her, \u201CCome over here and eat some bread
        and dip your bread in the vinegar.\u201D So she sat beside the reapers; and
        he served her roasted grain, and she ate until she was satisfied and she
        had some left [for Naomi]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "When she got up to glean, Boaz ordered his servants, \u201CLet her
        glean even among the sheaves, and do not insult her. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Also you shall purposely pull out for her some stalks [of grain]
        from the sheaves and leave them so that she may collect them, and do not
        rebuke her.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'So she gleaned in the field until evening. Then she beat out what
        she had gleaned, and it was about an ephah of barley. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'She picked it up and went into the city, and her mother-in-law saw
        what she had gleaned. Ruth also took out and gave to Naomi what she had saved
        after she [had eaten and] was satisfied. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Her mother-in-law said to her, \u201CWhere did you glean today? Where
        did you work? Blessed be the man who took notice of you.\u201D So she told
        her mother-in-law with whom she had worked and said, \u201CThe name of the
        man with whom I worked today is Boaz.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Naomi said to her daughter-in-law, \u201CMay he be blessed of the
        Lord who has not ceased His kindness to the living and to the dead.\u201D
        Again Naomi said to her, \u201CThe man is one of our closest relatives, one
        who has the right to redeem us.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Then Ruth the Moabitess said, \u201CHe also said to me, \u2018Stay
        close to my servants until they have harvested my entire crop.\u2019\u2009\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Naomi said to Ruth, \u201CIt is good, my daughter, for you to go
        out [to work] with his maids, so that others do not assault you in another
        field.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: So she stayed close to the maids of Boaz, gleaning until the end of
        the barley and wheat harvests. And she lived with her mother-in-law.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Boaz Will Redeem Ruth'
      title: Boaz Will Redeem Ruth
      number: 1
      content: "  Then Naomi her mother-in-law said to Ruth, \u201CMy daughter, shall
        I not look for security and a home for you, so that it may be well with you? "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Now Boaz, with whose maids you were [working], is he not our relative?
        See now, he is winnowing barley at the threshing floor tonight. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "So wash and anoint yourself [with olive oil], then put on your [best]
        clothes, and go down to the threshing floor; but stay out of the man\u2019s
        sight until he has finished eating and drinking. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "When he lies down, notice the place where he is lying, and go and
        uncover his feet and lie down. Then he will tell you what to do.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Ruth answered her, \u201CI will do everything that you say.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'So she went down to the threshing floor and did just as her mother-in-law
        had told her. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'When Boaz had eaten and drunk and his heart was happy, he went to
        lie down at the end of the stack of grain. Then Ruth came secretly, and uncovered
        his feet and lay down. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'In the middle of the night the man was startled and he turned over,
        and found a woman lying at his feet. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "So he said, \u201CWho are you?\u201D And she answered, \u201CI am
        Ruth your maid. Spread the hem of your garment over me, for you are a close
        relative and redeemer.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Then he said, \u201CMay you be blessed by the Lord, my daughter.
        You have made your last kindness better than the first; for you have not
        gone after young men, whether poor or rich. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Now, my daughter, do not be afraid. I will do for you whatever you
        ask, since all my people in the city know that you are a woman of excellence. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'It is true that I am your close relative and redeemer; however, there
        is a relative closer [to you] than I. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Spend the night [here], and in the morning if he will redeem you,
        fine; let him do it. But if he does not wish to redeem you, then, as the
        Lord lives, I will redeem you. Lie down until the morning.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "So she lay at his feet until the morning, but got up before anyone
        could recognize another; Boaz said, \u201CDo not let it be known that the
        woman came to the threshing floor [last night].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "He also said, \u201CGive me the shawl you are wearing and hold it
        out.\u201D So Ruth held it and he measured out six measures of barley [into
        it] and placed it on her. And she went into the city. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "When she came home, her mother-in-law said, \u201CHow did it go,
        my daughter?\u201D And Ruth told her everything that the man had done for
        her. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "She said, \u201CHe gave me these six measures of barley, and he said
        to me, \u2018Do not go back to your mother-in-law empty-handed.\u2019\u2009\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Then Naomi said, \u201CSit and wait, my daughter, until you learn
        how this matter turns out; for the man will not rest until he has settled
        it today.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Marriage of Ruth'
      title: The Marriage of Ruth
      number: 1
      content: "  Then Boaz went up to the city gate [where business and legal matters
        were settled] and sat down, and then the close relative (redeemer) of whom
        Boaz had spoken came by. He said to him, \u201CCome over here, friend, and
        sit down.\u201D So he came and sat down. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Then Boaz took ten men from the elders of the city and said, \u201CSit
        down here.\u201D And they sat down. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "He said to the closest relative (redeemer), \u201CNaomi, who has
        returned from the country of Moab, must sell the plot of land which belonged
        to our brother Elimelech. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "So I thought to let you hear of it, saying, \u2018Buy it in the presence
        of those sitting here, and before the elders of my people. If you will redeem
        it, redeem it; but if not, then tell me, so that I may know; for there is
        no one besides you to redeem it, and I am [next of kin] after you.\u2019\u2009\u201D
        And he said, \u201CI will redeem it.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then Boaz said, \u201CThe day that you buy the field from Naomi,
        you must also acquire Ruth the Moabitess, the widow of the deceased, to restore
        the name of the deceased to his inheritance.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "The closest relative (redeemer) said, \u201CI cannot redeem it for
        myself, because [by marrying a Moabitess] I would jeopardize my own inheritance.
        Take my right of redemption (purchase) yourself, because I cannot redeem
        it.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Now formerly in Israel this was the custom concerning redeeming and
        exchanging property. To confirm a transaction, a man pulled off his sandal
        and gave it to the other. This was the way of confirming and attesting in
        Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "So, when the closest relative (redeemer) said to Boaz, \u201CBuy
        it for yourself,\u201D he pulled off his sandal [and gave it to Boaz to confirm
        the agreement]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then Boaz said to the elders and to all the people, \u201CYou are
        witnesses this day that I have bought everything that was Elimelech\u2019s
        and everything that was Chilion\u2019s and Mahlon\u2019s from the hand of
        Naomi. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "I have also acquired Ruth the Moabitess, the widow of Mahlon, to
        be my wife to restore the name of the deceased to his inheritance, so that
        the name of the deceased will not be cut off from his brothers or from the
        gate of his birthplace. You are witnesses today.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "All the people at the gate and the elders said, \u201CWe are witnesses.
        May the Lord make the woman who is coming into your house like Rachel and
        Leah, the two who built the household of Israel. May you achieve wealth and
        power in Ephrathah and become famous in Bethlehem. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Further, may your house be like the house of Perez whom Tamar bore
        to Judah, because of the offspring which the Lord will give you by this young
        woman.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'So Boaz took Ruth, and she became his wife. And he went in to her,
        and the Lord enabled her to conceive, and she gave birth to a son. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Then the women said to Naomi, \u201CBlessed is the Lord who has not
        left you without a redeemer (grandson, as heir) today, and may his name become
        famous in Israel. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: The Line of David Began Here'
      title: The Line of David Began Here
      number: 15
      content: "May he also be to you one who restores life and sustains your old
        age; for your daughter-in-law, who loves you and is better to you than seven
        sons, has given birth to him.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Then Naomi took the child and placed him in her lap, and she became
        his nurse. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "The neighbor women gave him a name, saying, \u201CA son (grandson)
        has been born to Naomi.\u201D They named him Obed (worshiper). He is the
        father of Jesse, the father of David [the ancestor of Jesus Christ].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Now these are the descendants of Perez: Perez was the father of Hezron, '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Hezron was the father of Ram, Ram the father of Amminadab, '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Amminadab the father of Nahshon, Nahshon the father of Salmon, '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Salmon the father of Boaz, Boaz the father of Obed, '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: Obed the father of Jesse, and Jesse the father of David [the king
        of Israel and the ancestor of Jesus Christ].
      comments: []
